rComments: Professeure Pilote est un très bon professeur. Très intéressant et très divertissant lorsquil enseigne ces cours. Il associe souvent des exemples de la vie courant à la matière présenté, ce qui rend les choses beaucoup moins abstraites. Si vous faites les lectures assignés et que vous vous présentez en classe, ces examens sont très faciles.

Despite English not being his first language, I found Guillaume was an excellent lecturer. His lectures were engaging, he provided thoughtful real-life examples to relate the course material, and he essentially told us exactly what would be on every exam. Anybody that thought 1104 with him was hard was simply lazy and didn't pay attention.
teacherRatingTags: ['Clear grading criteria', 'Amazing lectures ', 'Beware of pop quizzes']

rComments: Prof. Pilote is a very nice professor, makes himself easily accesible to students. Lectures are a little dry some times, he clearly knows the subject really well but doesn't always convey it in an interesting way - not to say he doesn't make an effort, though. He (or his T.A., not sure) is a very, very hard marker. Not an easy course.

Lecture are long, hard to follow and not especially stimulating. He seems to know what he's talking about but does not clearly get the point across. You will also write the most boring essay you will ever write.
teacherRatingTags: ['Beware of pop quizzes', 'Get ready to read', 'Lecture heavy']

rComments: Excellent prof! Il s'assure toujours que la classe comprends bien. Les lectures sont quand même asser dures, mais il trouve toujours une manière de faire un lien avec le quotidien, et celle-ci deviens facile après ses explications. Très disponible (horraires flexibles) réponds toujours à ces courriels. Les travaux et examens sont faciles. Loved it!

I really like this prof a lot.  His lectures are very organized and he is very interested in the subject matter.  He goes out of his way to help students who are struggling.  I learned a lot in his course.  He is always respectful and thoughtful about comments students make in the class.  Makes me way to take more philosophy!
